The formula derived from equating these forces is: \[ M = \frac{4 \pi^2 r^3}{G T^2} \] **Step-by-Step Calculation:** 1. **Convert the angular radius to radians:** \[ 0.12 \text{ arcseconds} = 0.12 \times \frac{\pi}{180 \times 3600} \approx 5.8178 \times 10^{-7} \text{ radians} \] 2. **Convert the distance to the Galactic center from kpc to meters:** \[ 8 \text{ kpc} = 8 \times 10^3 \times 3.0857 \times 10^{16} \approx 2.46856 \times 10^{20} \text{ meters} \] 3. **Calculate the actual orbital radius:** \[ r = 5.8178 \times 10^{-7} \times 2.46856 \times 10^{20} \approx 1.43578 \times 10^{14} \text{ meters} \] 4. **Convert the orbital period from years to seconds:** \[ 15 \text{ years} = 15 \times 3.15576 \times 10^7 \approx 4.7336 \times 10^8 \text{ seconds} \] 5. **Calculate the numerator \(4 \pi^2 r^3\):** \[ r^3 \approx (1.43578 \times 10^{14})^3 \approx 2.95838 \times 10^{42} \text{ m}^3 \] \[ 4 \pi^2 \times 2.95838 \times 10^{42} \approx 39.4784 \times 2.95838 \times 10^{42} \approx 1.1679 \times 10^{44} \text{ kg} \cdot \text{m}^2 \] 6. **Calculate the denominator \(G T^2\):** \[ G \times T^2 \approx 6.674 \times 10^{-11} \times (4.7336 \times 10^8)^2 \approx 1.49306 \times 10^7 \text{ m}^3 \cdot \text{kg}^{-1} \cdot \text{s}^{-2} \] 7. **Compute the mass of the black hole:** \[ M = \frac{1.1
